", "label": "Date"}, {"value": "<span>Caricature of a treatment better known as Perkins Tractors, named after its inventor, Elisha Perkins (1741-1799), an American physician. Two tapered rods made of different metals \u2013 normally brass and silver \u2013 were passed over the body and, it was claimed, drew out disease using electricity. The tractors were said to be charged from the natural electricity present in the user\u2019s body. Perkins patented his invention in 1796. Despite claims that Perkin\u2019s invention cured over five thousand people in England of various complaints, the treatment was widely discredited and was labelled by many as \u2018quackery\u2019.</span>", "label": "Description"}, {"value": "<span>Engraving</span>", "label": "Technique"}, {"value": "<span>Etching (hand-coloured)</span>", "label": "Secondary Technique"}, {"value": "<span>University of Edinburgh Main Library</span>", "label": "Location"}, {"value": "<span>Centre for Research Collections</span>", "label": "Department"}, {"value": "<span>Metalic tractors</span>", "label": "Subject"}, {"value": "<span>Medicine</span>", "label": "Subject Category"}, {"value": "<span>Caricature</span>", "label": "Subject"}, {"value": "<span>Humour</span>", "label": "Subject Category"}, {"value": "<span>Perkins, Elisha</span>", "label": "Subject"}, {"value": "<span>Medicine</span>", "label": "Subject Category"}, {"value": "<span>Digital Image: Copyright \u00a9 The University of Edinburgh. Original: Out of Copyright.</span>", "label": "Rights Statement"}, {"value": "<span>Thomson-Walker Collection</span>", "label": "Provenance Notes"}, {"value": "<span>Medicine</span>", "label": "Tag"}, {"value": "<span>Portraits</span>", "label": "Tag"}, {"value": "<span>Science and Natural History</span>", "label": "Tag"}, {"value": "<span>Archives</span>", "label": "Tag"}, {"value": "<span>Cropped Tiff</span>", "label": "Repro File Type"}, {"value": "<span>165074844</span>", "label": "Repro File Size (bytes)"}, {"value